---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';

const npmInitCode = `import Oopsie from 'oopsie-sdk';

Oopsie.init({
  serverUrl: 'https://oopsie.example.com',
  apiKey: 'your_project_api_key',
});`;

const cdnCode = `<script src="https://unpkg.com/oopsie-sdk"></script>
<script>
  Oopsie.init({
    serverUrl: 'https://oopsie.example.com',
    apiKey: 'your_project_api_key',
  });
</script>`;
---

<DocsLayout title="SDK Installation">
  <p>Install the Oopsie SDK in your application using npm or a CDN script tag.</p>

  <h2>npm</h2>
  <pre><code>npm install oopsie-sdk</code></pre>
  <pre><code class="language-javascript" set:text={npmInitCode} /></pre>

  <h2>CDN</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-html" set:text={cdnCode} /></pre>
  <h2>npm registry</h2>
  <p>The package is available on <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/oopsie-sdk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">npmjs.com/package/oopsie-sdk</a>.</p>

  <h2>Output formats</h2>
  <p>The SDK is distributed in three formats:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>ESM</strong> — For modern bundlers (Vite, webpack, etc.)</li>
    <li><strong>CJS</strong> — For CommonJS environments (Node.js)</li>
    <li><strong>IIFE</strong> — For direct browser usage via script tag</li>
  </ul>

